<!--
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
→ XML declaration (standard header for XML files)

<paths>
→ Root element required by FileProvider
→ Defines which directories/files your app is allowed to share securely

<cache-path
    name="pdf_cache"
    path="." />

Explanation:

cache-path
→ Refers to your app’s internal cache directory:
   /data/data/<your-app>/cache/
→ Files here are temporary and can be cleared by the system

name="pdf_cache"
→ Logical name (alias) used to identify this path
→ Used when generating content URIs (not an actual folder name)

path="."
→ "." means the ROOT of the cache directory
→ So all files inside cache/ are allowed to be shared

Purpose:
→ Allows your app to share files (like PDFs) stored in cache
→ Required for FileProvider to generate secure content:// URIs

Example actual path:
→ /data/data/com.jobportal.resumematching/cache/yourfile.pdf

Security:
→ Only files inside declared paths can be shared
→ Prevents exposing sensitive internal storage

Common use case:
→ Save PDF in cache → share via Intent → FileProvider gives safe URI
-->
<paths>
    <cache-path name="pdf_cache" path="." />
</paths>